{
  "text": "There is an understanding that the treatment of the dentin sensitivity mainly has being focused on the tubular occlusion [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . For the sealing of the dentinal tubules, there is the method of using a smear layer that can decrease the level of dentin permeability by 98%, when compared to dentin treated with acid [CITATION_3] . Regarding the SEM analysis of the control group, the micrographs showed closed dentinal tubules by the smear layer and 90% of cohesive failures in the resin cement (Figure 1) .",
  "correct_citation": {
